      },
      "source": [
        "# Training R-CNN-based custom object detectors"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5Kpg4ECKwWss"
      },
      "source": [
        "R-CNN stands for Region-based Convolutional Neural Network. Region-based within R-CNN stands for the region proposals. Region proposals are used to identify objects within an image. Note that R-CNN assists in identifying both the objects present in the image and the location of objects within the image.\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "In this notebook, we will learn about the working details of R-CNN before training it on our custom dataset."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "I71DsBMqyLKB"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Setup"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kGxjEtGiyMj-"
      },
      "source": [
        "!pip install -q --upgrade selectivesearch torch_snippets"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "T6QlWQZCyQ4F"
      },
      "source": [
        "from torch_snippets import *\r\n",

      ],

      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "CUZO9wj1yzP6"
      },
      "source": [
        "from torchvision import transforms, models, datasets\r\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "90XjSafPzEPZ"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Working details of R-CNN"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jofZWDs0zFIj"
      },
      "source": [
        "Let's get an idea of R-CNN-based object detection at a high level using the following diagram:\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "<img src='https://github.com/rahiakela/img-repo/blob/master/object-detection-images/r-cnn-arch.png?raw=1' width='800'/>\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "We perform the following steps when leveraging the R-CNN technique for object detection:\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "1. Extract region proposals from an image:\r\n",
        "  - Ensure that we extract a high number of proposals to not miss out on any potential object within the image.\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "2. Resize (warp) all the extracted regions to get images of the same size.\r\n",
        "3. Pass the resized region proposals through a network:\r\n",
        "  - Typically, we pass the resized region proposals through a pretrained model such as VGG16 or ResNet50 and extract the features in a fully connected layer.\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "4. Create data for model training, where the input is features extracted by passing the region proposals through a pretrained model, and the outputs are the class corresponding to each region proposal and the offset of the region proposal from the ground truth corresponding to the image:\r\n",
        "  - If a region proposal has an IoU greater than a certain threshold with the object, we prepare training data in such a way that the region is responsible for predicting the class of object it is overlapping with and also the offset of region proposal with the ground truth bounding box that contains the object of interest.\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "A sample as a result of creating a bounding box offset and a ground truth class for a region proposal is as follows:\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "<img src='https://github.com/rahiakela/img-repo/blob/master/object-detection-images/region-proposal.png?raw=1' width='800'/>\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "In the preceding image, o (in red) represents the center of the region proposal (dotted bounding box) and x represents the center of the ground truth bounding box (solid bounding box) corresponding to the cat class. We calculate the offset between the region proposal bounding box and the ground truth bounding box as the difference between center co-ordinates of the two bounding boxes (dx, dy) and the difference between the height and width of the bounding boxes (dw, dh).\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "5. Connect two output heads, one corresponding to the class of image and the other corresponding to the offset of region proposal with the ground truth bounding box to extract the fine bounding box on the object:\r\n",
        "  - This exercise would be similar to the use case where we predicted gender (categorical variable, analogous to the class of object in this case study) and age (continuous variable, analogous to the offsets to be done on top of region proposals) based on the image of the face of a person.\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "6. Train the model post, writing a custom loss function that minimizes both object classification error and the bounding box offset error.\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "Note that the loss function that we will minimize differs from the loss function that is optimized in the original paper. We are doing this to reduce the complexity associated with building R-CNN and Fast R-CNN from scratch. Once the reader is familiar with how the model works and can build a model using the following code, we highly encourage them to implement the original paper from scratch."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "t6REWk5I3yfn"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Implementing R-CNN for object detection on a custom dataset"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9ykNYX8l3zkW"
      },
      "source": [
        "So far, we have a theoretical understanding of how R-CNN works. In this section, we will learn about creating data for training. This process involves the following steps:\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "1. Downloading the dataset\r\n",
        "2. Preparing the dataset\r\n",
        "3. Defining the region proposals extraction and IoU calculation functions\r\n",
        "4. Creating the training data\r\n",
        "  - Creating input data for the model\r\n",
        "    - Resizing the region proposals\r\n",
        "    - Passing them through a pretrained model to fetch the fully connected layer values\r\n",
        "  - Creating output data for the model\r\n",
        "    - Labeling each region proposal with a class or background label\r\n",
        "    - Defining the offset of the region proposal from the ground truth if the region proposal corresponds to an object and not background\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "5. Defining and training the model\r\n",
        "6. Predicting on new images"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "### Preparing the dataset"
      ]

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Un6exff47qO9"
      },
      "source": [
        "Now that we have downloaded the dataset, we will prepare the dataset. This involves the following steps:\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "1. Fetching each image and its corresponding class and bounding box values\r\n",
        "2. Fetching the region proposals within each image, their corresponding IoU, and the delta by which the region proposal is to be corrected with respect to the ground truth\r\n",
        "3. Assigning numeric labels for each class (where we have an additional background class (besides the bus and truck classes) where IoU with the ground truth bounding box is below a threshold)\r\n",
        "4. Resizing each region proposal to a common size in order to pass them to a network\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "By the end of this exercise, we will have resized crops of region proposals, along with assigning the ground truth class to each region proposal, and calculated the offset of the region proposal in relation to the ground truth bounding box. \r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "1. Specify the location of images and read the ground truths present in the CSV file that we downloaded:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "lMyTPvTz8RNf",
        "outputId": "7c28c061-c83d-46cd-cb09-9532ccfee7c5"
      },
      "source": [
        "IMAGE_ROOT = \"images/images/\"\r\n",
        "DF_RAW = pd.read_csv(\"df.csv\")\r\n",
        "print(DF_RAW.head())"
      ],
      "execution_count": 6,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [

            "1  00006bdb1eb5cd74  xclick     Truck  ...  0.241855  0.352130  0.437343\n",
            "2  00006bdb1eb5cd74  xclick     Truck  ...  0.398496  0.409774  0.295739\n",
            "3  00010bf498b64bab  xclick       Bus  ...  0.493882  0.705228  0.521691\n",
            "4  00013f14dd4e168f  xclick       Bus  ...  0.303940  0.999062  0.523452\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4lXZsltx8_Iq"
      },
      "source": [
        "Note that `XMin`, `XMax`, `YMin`, and `YMax` correspond to the ground truth of the bounding box of the image. Furthermore, LabelName provides the class of image.\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "2. Define a class that returns the image and its corresponding class and ground truth along with the file path of the image:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kDFKiPlE8h2M"
      },
      "source": [
        "class OpenImages(Dataset):\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "  def __init__(self, df, image_folder=IMAGE_ROOT):\r\n",
        "    self.root = image_folder\r\n",
        "    self.df = df\r\n",
        "    self.unique_images = df[\"ImageID\"].unique()\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "  def __len__(self):\r\n",
        "    return len(self.unique_images)\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "  def __getitem__(self, idx):\r\n",
        "    image_id = self.unique_images[idx]\r\n",
        "    image_path = f\"{self.root}/{image_id}.jpg\"\r\n",
        "    image = cv2.imread(image_path, 1)[..., ::-1]   # conver BGR to RGB\r\n",
        "    h, w, _ = image.shape\r\n",
        "    df = self.df.copy()\r\n",
        "    df = df[df[\"ImageID\"] == image_id]\r\n",
        "    boxes = df[\"XMin,YMin,XMax,YMax\".split(\",\")].values\r\n",
        "    boxes = (boxes * np.array([w, h, w, h])).astype(np.uint16).tolist()\r\n",
        "    classes = df[\"LabelName\"].values.tolist()\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "    return image,boxes, classes, image_path"
      ],
      "execution_count": 7,
      "outputs": []
    },

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "CJbJyZf9A3KT"
      },
      "source": [
        "4.Define the extract_iou and extract_candidates functions:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jecZ6m1U_t-t"
      },
      "source": [
        "def extract_candidates(img):\r\n",
        "  img_label, regions = selectivesearch.selective_search(img, scale=200, min_size=100)\r\n",
        "  img_area = np.prod(img.shape[:2])\r\n",
        "  candidates = []\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "  for r in regions:\r\n",
        "    if r[\"rect\"] in candidates:\r\n",
        "      continue\r\n",
        "    if r[\"size\"] < (0.05 * img_area):\r\n",
        "      continue\r\n",
        "    if r[\"size\"] > (1 * img_area):\r\n",
        "      continue\r\n",
        "    x, y, w, h = r[\"rect\"]\r\n",
        "    candidates.append(list(r[\"rect\"]))\r\n",
        "  return candidates"
      ],
      "execution_count": 10,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jkCddgyDB_lv"
      },
      "source": [
        "def extract_iou(boxA, boxB, epsilon=1e-5):\r\n",
        "  x1 = max(boxA[0], boxB[0])\r\n",
        "  x2 = max(boxA[1], boxB[1])\r\n",
        "  y1 = min(boxA[2], boxB[2])\r\n",
        "  y2 = min(boxA[3], boxB[3])\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "  width = (x2 - x1)\r\n",
        "  height = (y2 - y1)\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "  if (width < 0) or (height > 0):\r\n",
        "    return 0.0\r\n",
        "  \r\n",
        "  area_overlap = width * height\r\n",
        "  area_a = (boxA[2] - boxA[0]) * (boxA[3] - boxA[1])\r\n",
        "  area_b = (boxB[2] - boxB[0]) * (boxB[3] - boxB[1])\r\n",
        "  area_combined = area_a + area_b - area_overlap\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "  iou = area_overlap / (area_combined + epsilon)\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "  return iou"
      ],
      "execution_count": 11,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3QsFYzPtDv4a"
      },
      "source": [
        "By now, we have defined all the functions necessary to prepare data and initialize data loaders."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "UFDoPrLpDprB"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Defining the region proposals extraction and IoU calculation functions"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "07ZdE43cDrPY"
      },
      "source": [
        "we will learn about creating the input and output values corresponding to our model. The input constitutes the candidates that are extracted using the selectivesearch method and the output constitutes the class corresponding to candidates and the offset of the candidate with respect to the bounding box it overlaps the most with if the candidate contains an object.\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "**1.** Initialize empty lists to store file paths, ground truth bounding boxes , classes of objects, the delta offset of a bounding box with region proposals, region proposal locations, and the IoU of region proposals with ground truths:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "oD_gaj76DXzk"
      },
      "source": [
        "FILE_PATHS, GTBBS, CLAZZ, DELTAS, ROIS, IOUS = [], [], [], [], [], []"
      ],
      "execution_count": 12,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MikjHYEI31WE"
      },
      "source": [
        "**2.**Loop through the dataset and populate the lists initialized above:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "clIh_hya35ic"
      },
      "source": [
        "N = 500\r\n",
        "for idx, (im, bbs, labels, fpath) in enumerate(ds):\r\n",
        "  if(idx == N):\r\n",
        "    break\r\n",
        "  H, W, _ = im.shape\r\n",
        "  # Extract candidates from each image \r\n",
        "  candidates = extract_candidates(im)\r\n",
        "  candidates = np.array([(x, y, x + w, y + h) for x, y, w, h in candidates])\r\n",
        "  ious, rois, clss, deltas = [], [], [], []\r\n",
        "  # Store the IoU of all candidates with respect to all ground truths for an image \r\n",
        "  ious = np.array([[extract_iou(candidate, _bb_) for candidate in candidates] for _bb_ in bbs]).T\r\n",
        "  # Loop through each candidate\r\n",
        "  for jx, candidate in enumerate(candidates):\r\n",
        "    cx, cy, cX, cY = candidate\r\n",
        "    # Extract the IoU corresponding to the candidate\r\n",
        "    candidate_ious = ious[jx]\r\n",
        "    # Find the index of a candidate that has the highest IoU and the corresponding ground truth \r\n",
        "    best_iou_at = np.argmax(candidate_ious)\r\n",
        "    best_iou = candidate_ious[best_iou_at]\r\n",
        "    best_bb = _x, _y, _X, _Y = bbs[best_iou_at]\r\n",
        "\r\n",
        "    # If IoU (best_iou) is greater than a threshold (0.3), we assign the label of class corresponding to the candidate, and the background otherwise\r\n",
        "    if best_iou > 0.3:\r\n",
        "      clss.append(labels[best_iou_at])\r\n",
        "    else:\r\n",
        "      clss.append(\"background\")\r\n",
        "    # Fetch the offsets needed (delta) to transform the current proposal into the candidate that is the best region proposal-best_bb\r\n",
        "    delta = np.array([_x - cx, _y - cy, _X - cX, _Y - cY]) / np.array([W, H, W, H])\r\n",
        "    deltas.append(delta)\r\n",
        "    rois.append(candidate / np.array([W, H, W, H]))\r\n",
        "  FILE_PATHS.append(fpath)\r\n",
        "  IOUS.append(ious)\r\n",
        "  ROIS.append(rois)\r\n",
        "  CLAZZ.append(clss)\r\n",
        "  DELTAS.append(deltas)\r\n",
        "  GTBBS.append(bbs)"
      ],
